           "description":"\u003cp\u003eDevOps Engineer\n(Austin, TX)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAbout Atmosphere:\nAtmosphere is the world’s first and largest free ad-supported streaming TV service for businesses offering original, owned, and operated TV channels along with Partner Channels from prominent brands. The platform has been built from the ground up with proprietary content, technology, and data to deliver unparalleled experiences for businesses and advertisers. The platform also provides a paid upgrade to a digital signage feature for businesses to run their house promotions within the content. Atmosphere was incubated under Chive Media Group and spun out in 2019.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAbout this role:\nAtmosphere is growing fast - which means our Engineering team has to be one step ahead when it comes to providing a stellar product and anticipating our customers' needs. As we expand our offering we need an experienced engineer with a particular focus on Python 3, Django REST Framework, and Puppet. This position reports to Atmosphere's Director of DevOps.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eYou MUST reside in the Austin, TX area for consideration.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSKILLS \u0026amp; REQUIREMENTS:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMust have experience with automation and configuration management using Puppet, Ansible, or Chef\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStrong grasp of modern Python development (3.6+)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with Django and the Django REST Framework\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStrong background in Linux/Unix Administration is a must\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFamiliarity with Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery pipelines\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience managing software releases across multiple git repositories\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with relational, non-relational, and time-series data stores (MySQL, MongoDB, Redis, Elasticsearch)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eKnowledge of MySQL database replication methods, particularly Group Replication, preferred\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDeep knowledge of Google Cloud Platform and AWS\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSolid understanding of DNS, HTTP, TCP\\IP, Networking and VPNs\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eGRAVY: Some Ruby/JRuby experience, CentOS/RHEL experience, and knowledge of building rpm packages\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCOMPENSATION \u0026amp; BENEFITS:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCompetitive salary + commission\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCompany equity\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCompetitive insurance\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eCompany 401(k)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOpen vacation policy\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDog friendly\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eLunch 3 times a week at HQ\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDynamic office environment\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSo much more!\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n",
           "how_to_apply":"\u003cp\u003eApply directly at \u003ca href=\"https://atmosphere.tv/careers/job-description?gnk=job\u0026amp;gni=8a7887a875953d9f0175af7efaa51b80\"\u003ehttps://atmosphere.tv/careers/job-description?gnk=job\u0026amp;gni=8a7887a875953d9f0175af7efaa51b80\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n",
