           "description":"\u003cp\u003eQuick Take: Axios is a growth-stage startup dedicated to providing trustworthy, award-winning news content in an audience-first format. We're hiring a Data Quality Engineer!\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWhy it Matters: The quality team’s mission at Axios will be to ensure our technology is of the highest quality for our readers and clients every day. In this role you will be collaborating with multi-functional teams such as the data engineering, data science and product teams to test, validate and monitor data platforms and the data flowing through them. The quality team will integrate tightly into our cross-functional product teams to refine requirements for our products and to ensure the systems delivered line up.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe Details: The Data Quality Engineer’s responsibility is to ensure Axios is shipping better products consistently. Responsibilities of this role include:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCollaborating with technical leads, data engineers, analysts, product managers and assigned squad to define and refine requirements\nLeading the squad’s efforts in identifying risk and developing mitigation strategies\nDeveloping methods for managing and maintaining data integrity across systems\nWriting and executing test plans, utilizing both manual and automated testing techniques\nManaging bugs, including identification, logging, tracking and triaging\nWorking with data engineering squad to prioritize and develop data qualification pipeline, qualification criteria, identify testing gaps, and deliver measurable test results\nIdentifying the need for and improving processes, tools and testing \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eGo Deeper: Ideal candidates will embody an entrepreneurial spirit, a passion for Axios’ mission and have the following skills:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eExperience detecting and reporting data quality issues\nExperience in Software Quality Assurance, Quality Engineering, or as a SDET\nExperience working with data pipeline/pipeline issues\nFamiliarity with Kafka, PySpark, Jenkins/Circle, AWS\nExperience testing services and web applications\nWillingness to be a problem solver and produce results in a fast paced environment\nExperience working with Ruby, Python, Node and/or Javascript is preferred\nPractical experience with SQL and NoSQL databases\nThe ability to set up test environments, deploy code, use the command line\nExperience testing in an Agile and Continuous Integration environment\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills\nExceptionally collaborative with obsessive attention to detail\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eDon’t forget:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eCompetitive salary\nHealth insurance (100% paid for individuals, 75% for families)\nPrimary caregiver 12-week paid leave\n401K\nGenerous vacation policy, plus company holidays\nCompany equity\nCommuter and cell phone benefit\nA commitment to an open, inclusive, and diverse work culture\nAnnual learning and development stipend\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAdditional pandemic-related benefits:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOne mental health day per month\n$100 monthly work-from-home stipend\nTele-mental health services \nOneMedical membership, including tele-health services \nIncreased work flexibility for parents and caretakers \nAccess to the Axios “Family Fund”, which was created to allow employees to request financial support when facing financial hardship or emergencies \nWeekly company-sponsored exercise and meditation classes \nVirtual company-sponsored social events\u003c/p\u003e\n",
           "how_to_apply":"\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://grnh.se/0fc8c27a1us\"\u003ehttps://grnh.se/0fc8c27a1us\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n",
